subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus (
Fig. 10–12
) elongate, with paramera round and moderately widened apically and, in lateral view, distinctly acuminate toward apex.

Epipharynx (
Fig. 13
) transverse, round at sides; epitorma oval; corypha with two stout apical celtes as long as, or little more, acropariae.
